data.meta_description: Kirghiz Soviet Socialist Republic. The Kyrgyz State Historical Museum located in Bishkek. The modern building, where the museum is now located, was built to accommodate the Branch of the Museum named after V. I. Lenin in 1984 for the 60th anniversary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Kyrgyzstan according to the project of the staff of the Institute "Kirgizgiprostroy". The project was designed by the architects: S. Abyshev, R. Asylbekov, A. Kudeli, V. Ivanov and M. Satybaldiev.
